NNLO QCD corrections to leptonic observables in top-quark pair production and decay

Fiducial phase space corresponding to section 3.3 in JHEP 05 (2021) 212 (arxiv:2008.11133)
Plus pT(nnbar) > 40 GeV requirement for same-flavour leptons

Authors: Czakon, Generet, Mitov, Poncelet

Contact:  mczakon@physik.rwth-aachen.de
          terry.generet@rwth-aachen.de
          adm74@cam.ac.uk
          poncelet@hep.phy.cam.ac.uk

Model parameters:
mt = 172.5 GeV
mW = 80.385 GeV
mZ = 91.1876 GeV
GW = 2.0928 GeV
Gt = (1.48063 - 1.18*aS - 2.65*aS^2) GeV
GF = 1.166379*10^-5 GeV^-2
nf = 5 (massless b-quarks)

PDF:
  LO   : NNPDF31_lo_as_0118
  NLO  : NNPDF31_nlo_as_0118
  NNLO : NNPDF31_nnlo_as_0118

Scales: muR = HT/4, muF = HT/4

All histograms are given as a list of bins with the data format in case of absolute distributions ([X]: energy unit of observable; the last two columns are only present at NNLO):

Units : [X]      [X]       pb/[X]        pb/[X]   pb/[X]     pb/[X]        pb/[X]  pb/[X]
Values: edge-low edge-high scale_central scale_up scale_down mcerr_central PDF_up  PDF_down

in case of 2D:

Units : [X]           [X]            [Y]           [Y]            pb/[X]/[Y]    pb/[X]/[Y] pb/[X]/[Y] pb/[X]/[Y]    pb/[X]/[Y] pb/[X]/[Y]
Values: edge-dim1-low edge-dim1-high edge-dim2-low edge-dim2-high scale_central scale_up   scale_down mcerr_central PDF_up     PDF_down

Each file name is constructed after the pattern: <phasespace>_<order>_mt<mass>_<scale>_<pdf>_<obs>.dat  
<phasespace> : fid
<order>      : LO,NLO,NNLO
<mass>       : 172.5
<scale>      : HT4
<pdf>        : NNPDF31
<obs>        :
  pTnnbar
  dphilnnbar
  pTnnbar_x_dphilnnbar